      This function creates a button with specified dimensions, label, and press action.
      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate of the button's top-left corner.
      y - The y parameter represents the vertical position of the button on the screen or component. It is usually measured in pixels from the top of the screen or component.
      width - The width parameter is an integer value that represents the desired width of the button in pixels.
      height - The height parameter is an integer value that represents the height of the button in pixels.
      label - The label parameter is a Component object that represents the text or image that will be displayed on the button. It can be a simple text string or a more complex graphical element.
      pressAction - `pressAction` is a functional interface that defines the action to be performed when the button is pressed. It typically takes no arguments and returns no value. The implementation of this interface is passed as a lambda expression or method reference when creating the button.
      Returns:
      A Button object is being returned.

    • createNumbersTextBox

      public static net.minecraft.client.gui.components.EditBox createNumbersTextBox(net.minecraft.client.gui.Font font, int x, int y, int width, int height, net.minecraft.network.chat.Component label)
      This function creates an EditBox for entering numbers with a filter to only allow numeric input.
      Parameters:
      font - The font to be used for the text in the EditBox.
      x - The x-coordinate of the top-left corner of the text box.
      y - The parameter "y" represents the vertical position of the EditBox on the screen or component. It is usually measured in pixels from the top of the screen or component.
      width - The width parameter specifies the width of the EditBox in pixels.
      height - The height parameter is the height of the EditBox component being created.
      label - The label parameter is a Component object that represents the label associated with the EditBox. It could be a JLabel or any other type of Component that can be added to a container.
      Returns:
      The method is returning an instance of the EditBox class with a filter that only allows input of numbers (as a string).
